name: TimeRanges
description: The TimeRanges interface is used to represent a set of time ranges, primarily for the purpose of tracking which portions of media have been buffered when loading it for use by the <audio> and <video>Â elements.

members.name: TimeRanges.length
members.description: Returns an unsigned long representing the number of time ranges represented by the time range object.

members.name: TimeRanges.start()
members.description: Returns the time for the start of the range with the specified index.

parameters.name: INDEX_SIZE_ERR
parameters.description: A DOMException thrown if the specified index doesn't correspond to an existing range.

members.name: TimeRanges.end()
members.description: Returns the time for the end of the specified range.

parameters.name: INDEX_SIZE_ERR
parameters.description: A DOMException thrown if the specified index doesn't correspond to an existing range.
